alethinophidia.userInterface

Class Field

  • java.lang.Object
    • alethinophidia.userInterface.Field

  • public class Field
extends java.lang.Object
    It's an universal class for creating interface elements. Buttons, fields, bitmaps and such. Also holds instance of Transitions class witch allows for simple transition animations like fading or blinking. note: coordinates, width and height arguments in constructor are float values in scope from 0 to 1.0, where 0 means either left or upper edge of the screen, while 1.0 means right or lower edge.
    Author:
    £ukasz Piotrowski
